docs.abstract: The president’s comments about the Duchess of Sussex continued an Orwellian saga that he single-handedly created, forcefully denied and then revived.
docs.snippet: The president’s comments about the Duchess of Sussex continued an Orwellian saga that he single-handedly created, forcefully denied and then revived.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — By the time he left London on Wednesday, President Trump somehow ended his state visit there a full 360 degrees from where he started. Which was referring to the Duchess of Sussex, the American-born Meghan Markle, as “nasty.”

headline.main: An Orwellian Tale? Trump Denies, Then Confirms, ‘Nasty’ Comments About Meghan Markle
headline.print_headline: ‘Nasty’ or Not? Trump Comments Go Round and Round

docs.abstract: Over the past several days, the president and his former communications director have been locked in a public insult battle.
docs.snippet: Over the past several days, the president and his former communications director have been locked in a public insult battle.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Since his 11-day tenure as the White House communications director ended in 2017 after an infamously foul-mouthed interview, Anthony Scaramucci has spent the past two years carving out a reliable niche for himself: defending President Trump on television networks like CNN and MSNBC where he has few on-camera allies.

headline.main: ‘He’s Off the Rails’: Anthony Scaramucci, on Another Media Blitz, Criticizes Trump
headline.print_headline: Former Acolyte, on Media Blitz, Calls Trump ‘Off the Rails’

docs.abstract: After the president enlists Benjamin Netanyahu to deny entry to two Muslim members of Congress, both parties warn that bipartisan support for Israel is in danger.
docs.snippet: After the president enlists Benjamin Netanyahu to deny entry to two Muslim members of Congress, both parties warn that bipartisan support for Israel is in danger.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — By pushing Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel into barring an official visit by the first two Muslim women in Congress, President Trump is doubling down on a strategy aimed at dividing the Democratic Party and pushing some Jewish voters into the arms of Republicans.

headline.main: Trump and Netanyahu Put Bipartisan Support for Israel at Risk

docs.abstract: The president said on Twitter that he was reacting to the Danish prime minister’s rejection of his interest in buying Greenland from Denmark.
docs.snippet: The president said on Twitter that he was reacting to the Danish prime minister’s rejection of his interest in buying Greenland from Denmark.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Tuesday night abruptly canceled a coming trip to Denmark, writing on Twitter that because the country’s prime minister, Mette Frederiksen, “would have no interest in discussing the purchase of Greenland,” they would meet “another time.”

headline.main: Trump Scraps Trip to Denmark, as Greenland Is Not for Sale
headline.print_headline: Trump Scraps Denmark Trip As Greenland Is Not for Sale

docs.abstract: A federal judge sentenced Nicholas Slatten for murdering an Iraqi citizen, which prosecutors said prompted the shooting of dozens of Iraqis in Baghdad.
docs.snippet: A federal judge sentenced Nicholas Slatten for murdering an Iraqi citizen, which prosecutors said prompted the shooting of dozens of Iraqis in Baghdad.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Shortly before a federal judge sentenced him on Wednesday to life in prison for his role in the deadly 2007 shooting of dozens of unarmed Iraqis in Baghdad, Nicholas A. Slatten, a former Blackwater security contractor, stood in a tan jumpsuit and defiantly proclaimed that he was an innocent victim of Justice Department prosecutors run amok.

headline.main: Defiant Former Blackwater Contractor Again Sentenced to Life
headline.print_headline: Ex-Blackwater Contractor, Still Defiant, Gets Life Sentence in Iraq Killing
